INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2012-01-17 01:49:29','2012-01-17 01:49:29','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2012-01-17 04:07:36','2012-01-17 04:07:36','',0,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(47,1,'2012-01-19 20:51:24','2012-01-19 20:51:24','Send us your questions and contacts!\n<ul>\n	<li>Email: <a title=\"ihtconference@gmail.com\" href=\"mailto:ihtconference@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">ihtconference@gmail.com</a></li>\n	<li>Phone:</li>\n</ul>','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','21-autosave','','','2012-01-19 20:51:24','2012-01-19 20:51:24','',21,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=47',0,'revision','',0),(2,1,'2012-01-17 01:49:29','2012-01-17 01:49:29','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://ihtconference.com/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','open','','sample-page','','','2012-01-17 01:49:29','2012-01-17 01:49:29','',0,'http://ihtconference.com/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(3,1,'2012-01-17 01:50:54','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-01-17 01:50:54','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=3',0,'post','',0),(24,1,'2012-01-17 04:05:16','2012-01-17 04:05:16','http://ihtconference.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/header-logo.png','header-logo.png','','inherit','open','open','','header-logo-png','','','2012-01-17 04:05:16','2012-01-17 04:05:16','',0,'http://ihtconference.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/header-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(5,1,'2012-01-15 21:42:53','2012-01-15 21:42:53','Increasing health care costs and demand for health care services resulting from an aging and ailing population has made health care unaffordable and has undermined US businesses’ competitiveness in the global economy. Recently enacted health reforms aim to increase access to health care, decrease costs, and improve the quality of care. Innovation in health care technology—ranging from the implementation and use of HIT to the development of new medical devices—will change business models, improve efficiencies, and prove critical to the advancement of low cost, high quality health care. This conference will explore the role of innovation in health care technology in achieving an improved health care system.','Realizing the Future of Health Care','','publish','open','open','','hello-world-2','','','2012-01-19 21:31:11','2012-01-19 21:31:11','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=1',0,'post','',0),(53,1,'2012-01-19 21:32:12','2012-01-19 21:32:12','Increasing health care costs and demand for health care services resulting from an aging and ailing population has made health care unaffordable and has undermined US businesses’ competitiveness in the global economy. Recently enacted health reforms aim to increase access to health care, decrease costs, and improve the quality of care. Innovation in health care technology—ranging from the implementation and use of HIT to the development of new medical devices—will change business models, improve efficiencies, and prove critical to the advancement of low cost, high quality health care. This conference will explore the role of innovation in health care technology in achieving an improved health care system.','Realizing the Future of Health Care','','inherit','open','open','','5-autosave','','','2012-01-19 21:32:12','2012-01-19 21:32:12','',5,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=53',0,'revision','',0),(55,1,'2012-01-19 21:36:03','2012-01-19 21:36:03','<iframe width=\"650\" height=\"650\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;q=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Carnegie+Mellon+University,+Pittsburgh,+Allegheny,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;aq=&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.688845,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=0&amp;t=v&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;geocode=FXAeaQIdPTA8-w&amp;split=0&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Pittsburgh,+Allegheny,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;z=14&amp;ll=40.443504,-79.941571&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small><a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;q=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Carnegie+Mellon+University,+Pittsburgh,+Allegheny,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;aq=&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.688845,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=0&amp;t=v&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;geocode=FXAeaQIdPTA8-w&amp;split=0&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Pittsburgh,+Allegheny,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;z=14&amp;ll=40.443504,-79.941571\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">View Larger Map</a></small>','Directions','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-3','','','2012-01-19 21:36:03','2012-01-19 21:36:03','',49,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=55',0,'revision','',0),(54,1,'2012-01-19 20:58:15','2012-01-19 20:58:15','<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=5000+Forbes+Avenue,+Pittsburgh,+PA&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=5000+Forbes+Ave&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.688845,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;t=v&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Pittsburgh,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;ll=40.443504,-79.941571&amp;spn=0.011513,0.022724&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=A&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small><a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=5000+Forbes+Avenue,+Pittsburgh,+PA&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=5000+Forbes+Ave&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.688845,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;t=v&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=5000+Forbes+Ave,+Pittsburgh,+Pennsylvania+15213&amp;ll=40.443504,-79.941571&amp;spn=0.011513,0.022724&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=A\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">View Larger Map</a></small>','Directions','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-2','','','2012-01-19 20:58:15','2012-01-19 20:58:15','',49,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=54',0,'revision','',0),(56,1,'2012-01-19 21:38:07','2012-01-19 21:38:07','<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=40.4433,-79.942015&amp;num=1&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=40.44253,-79.943744&amp;spn=0.004083,0.005354&amp;z=17&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small><a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=40.4433,-79.942015&amp;num=1&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=40.44253,-79.943744&amp;spn=0.004083,0.005354&amp;z=17&amp;source=embed\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">View Larger Map</a></small>','Directions','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-4','','','2012-01-19 21:38:07','2012-01-19 21:38:07','',49,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=56',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2012-01-17 01:49:29','2012-01-17 01:49:29','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision','','','2012-01-17 01:49:29','2012-01-17 01:49:29','',1,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=25',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2012-01-15 23:07:26','2012-01-15 23:07:26','<h2>Rasu Shrestha</h2>\n<div>\n\nDr. Rasu Shrestha is the medical director of digital imaging informatics at UPMC who is focusing on the relationship between radiology (and other -oligy specialities) and information services to be implemented with the use of EMRs.  Dr. Shrestha will focus on the necessary synergy between health information technology and clinicians to provide a more patient-centric approach in healthcare.  Dr. Shrestha will address the benefits and barriers presented in implementing health IT in conjunction to the necessary changes that need to be made in today’s healthcare systems.\n<div>\n<h2>Don DeLauder</h2>\n<div>Don DeLauder, Executive Director of Corporate Innovation at Medrad, a leading medical device manufacturer focused on computed tomography, magnetic resonance, and cardiovascular applications, will provide a look into the future of the medical device industry. Mr. DeLauder will discuss future health care innovations, their impact on patients, and the barriers (e.g., regulations, product costs) and facilitators (ie. greater focus on customer centricity) to developing these devices. The address will conclude with recommendations for how innovators can achieve success in this future state.</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>','Keynote Speakers','','publish','open','open','','keynote','','','2012-01-15 23:07:26','2012-01-15 23:07:26','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(48,1,'2012-01-15 23:10:40','2012-01-15 23:10:40','This will hold the contact information for the team.','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision','','','2012-01-15 23:10:40','2012-01-15 23:10:40','',21,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=48',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2012-01-19 20:58:15','2012-01-19 20:58:15','<h2>Getting to Campus</h2>\r\nThe conference will be held on Carnegie Mellon University\'s campus in Pittsburgh and will be split between the University Center (denoted by the green arrow on the map below), Hamburg Hall, and Posner Hall.\r\n\r\nThe University Center is located at 5000 Forbes Ave, Pittsburgh, PA 15232.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Carnegie+Mellon+University&amp;aq=&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.956293,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;t=m&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=Carnegie+Mellon+University&amp;ll=40.458834,-79.958496&amp;spn=0.052245,0.117416&amp;z=13&amp;iwloc=A&amp;output=embed\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"685\" height=\"400\"></iframe>\r\n<small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Carnegie+Mellon+University&amp;aq=&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=48.956293,93.076172&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;t=m&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=Carnegie+Mellon+University&amp;ll=40.458834,-79.958496&amp;spn=0.052245,0.117416&amp;z=13&amp;iwloc=A\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n<h2>Parking</h2>\r\nParking is available in a garage next to the University Center at the intersection of Forbes and Beeler.\r\n<h2>Getting Around Campus</h2>\r\nHamburg Hall, home to the J. Heinz College, is located on Forbes Ave between S. Neville St and Morewood Ave. Posner Hall, home to the Tepper School of Business, is located at the corner of  Tech St and Frew St.\r\n\r\nPlease see the Carnegie Mellon University campus map for details about how to get around campus. Hamburg Hall is building 11, Posner Hall is building 19, and the University Center is building 29. The recommended parking garage is labeled P7.<a href=\"http://ihtconference.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/CMU_MapColor_11x17.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-63\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University Campus Map\" src=\"http://ihtconference.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/CMU_MapColor_11x17.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2564\" height=\"1643\" /></a>','Directions','','publish','open','open','','directions','','','2012-01-19 22:07:43','2012-01-19 22:07:43','',0,'http://ihtconference.com/?