3','The first annual Carnegie Mellon University Innovation in Health Care Technology Conference, presented by the J. Heinz College and the Tepper School of Business, will take place on March 23, 2012 on Carnegie Mellon\'s campus.','Realizing the Future of Health Care','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision','','','2012-01-15 21:42:53','2012-01-15 21:42:53','',5,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=52',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2012-01-15 23:09:23','2012-01-15 23:09:23','This is where we\'ll add information about the sponsors.','Sponsors','','publish','open','open','','sponsors','','','2012-01-15 23:09:23','2012-01-15 23:09:23','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2012-01-15 23:10:04','2012-01-15 23:10:04','<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td>9:00am-9:30am</td>\n<td>Registration and Continental Breakfast</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>University Center, Rangos 1, 2, and 3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td>9:30am-9:45am</td>\n<td>Welcome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>University Center, Rangos 1, 2, and 3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10:45am-11:15am</td>\n<td>Break</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td>11:15am-12:30pm</td>\n<td>Concurrent Panels: Medical Devices and Health Care IT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>Moving Medical Devices Beyond Its Current Capabilities to Drive High Quality, Low Cost Care</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>Hamburg Hall, Room 1000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n	<li>Moderator:</li>\n	<li>Christine Robbins, CEO, Body Media</li>\n	<li>Doug Ladd, Ethicon Endo Surgery</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>Moving HIT Beyond Its Current Capabilities to Drive Improved Patient Outcomes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>Posner Hall, Room 153</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"agendaHead\">\n<td></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n	<li>Moderator:</li>\n	<li>Eric Dahlem, Managing Director, Business Transformation Process, S