','2012-01-19 21:38:49','2012-01-19 21:38:49','',49,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=57',0,'revision','',0),(58,1,'2012-01-19 21:59:54','2012-01-19 21:59:54','<h2>Getting to Campus</h2>\r\nThe conference will be held on Carnegie Mellon University\'s campus in Pittsburgh and will be split between the University Center (denoted by the green arrow on the map below), Hamburg Hall, and Posner Hall.\r\n\r\nThe University Center is located at 5000 Forbes Ave, Pittsburgh, PA 15232.\r\n<h2>Parking</h2>\r\nParking is available in a garage next to the University Center at the intersection of Forbes and Beeler.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=40.4433,-79.942015&amp;num=1&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=40.442799,-79.944162&amp;spn=0.005716,0.00912&amp;z=16&amp;output=embed\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe>\r\n<small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=40.4433,-79.942015&amp;num=1&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=40.442799,-79.944162&amp;spn=0.005716,0.00912&amp;z=16&amp;source=embed\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n<h2>Getting Around Campus</h2>\r\nHamburg Hall, home to the J. Heinz College, is located on Forbes Ave between S. Neville St and Morewood Ave. Posner Hall, home to the Tepper School of Business, is located at the corner of  Tech St and Frew St.\r\n\r\nPlease see the Carnegie Mellon University campus map for details about how to get around campus. Hamburg Hall is building 11, Posner Hall is building 19, and the University Center is building 29. The recommended parking garage is labeled P7.','Directions','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-6','','','2012-01-19 21:59:54','2012-01-19 21:59:54','',49,'http://ihtconference.com/?p=58',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2012-01-15 23:08:33','2012-01-15 23:08:33','<div style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\" ><iframe  src=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/tickets-external?eid=2784405231&ref=etckt\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"192\" width=\"100%\" vspace=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" marginheight=\"5\" marginwidth=\"5\" scrolling=\"auto\" allowtransparency=\"true\"></iframe><div style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial; font-size:10px; padding:5px 0 5px; margin:2px; width:100%; text-align:left;\" ><a style=\"color:#ddd; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/r/etckt\" >Event management</a><span style=\"color:#ddd;\" > for </span><a style=\"color:#ddd; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://cmu-iht.eventbrite.com?ref=etckt\" >Carnegie Mellon University Innovation in Health Care Technology Conference</a><span style=\"color:#ddd;\" > powered by </span><a style=\"color:#ddd; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com?ref=etckt\" >Eventbrite</a></div></div>','Register','','publish','open','open','','register','','','2012-01-15 23:08:33','2012-01-15 23:08:33','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=15',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2012-01-15 23:08:00','2012-01-15 23:08:00','<div>\n<h2>Moving Medical Devices Beyond Its Current Capabilities to Drive High Quality Low Cost Care</h2>\n</div>\nTechnological advancement has been cited as a key driver of health care costs. This panel will discuss whether innovation in medical devices can improve efficiency and decrease systemic costs by improving the effectiveness of care, increasing patient engagement, and transforming health care providers’ business models.\n<h3>Panelists:</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Eric Dahlem, Managing Director, Business Transformation Process, SDLC Partners</li>\n	<li>Mary Anne Darragh, VP of Health Management Services, Highmark</li>\n	<li>Assaf Halevy, Co-founder and VP of Strategic Accounts and Business Development, dB Motion</li>\n	<li>Jay Srini, Chief Strategist, SCS Ventures</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Moving HIT Beyond Its Current Capabilities to Drive Improved Patient Outcomes</h2>\nThe Health IT field is continually growing to allow the sharing of patient information among healthcare providers in order to improve patient outcomes and decrease inefficiencies in care.  This panel will discuss the latest innovative Health IT solutions for more integrated healthcare and how they view this transition taking place.  The panelists will also provide insight on how the advancements in Health IT will serve consumers and end-users.\n<h3>Panelists:</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Christine Robbins, CEO, Body Media</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Building opportunities during uncertain economic and regulatory transition</h2>\nThese panelists represent start-up companies at various stages of funding and product development. After providing a brief overview of their company and business model, the panelists will discuss the challenges and opportunities arising from the economic downturn and increased regulation for entrepreneurs.\n<h3>Panelists:</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Hank Werronen (GSIA, ), PHQL</li>\n	<li>Adam Simone (MSBTM, 2011), Blue Belt Technologies</li>\n	<li>Steve Fleck, Clear Count  (still waiting confirmation)</li>\n</ul>','Panels','','publish','open','open','','panelists','','','2012-01-15 23:08:00','2012-01-15 23:08:00','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(59,1,'2012-01-19 22:00:46','2012-01-19 22:00:46','<h2>Getting to Campus</h2>\r\nThe conference will be held on Carnegie Mellon University\'s campus in Pittsburgh and will be split between the University Center (denoted by the green arrow on the map below), Hamburg Hall, and Posner Hall.\r\n\r\nThe University Center is located at 5000 Forbes Ave, Pittsburgh, PA 15232.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?q=40.4433,-79.942015&amp;num=1&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=40.442799,-79.944162&amp;spn=0.005716,0.00912&amp;z=16&amp;output=embed\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></iframe>\r\n<small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.goog